      "content": "I'm not being overly cautious, but as someone with CKD, it's always better to err on the side of caution. Even a low dose like 200mg is not negligible, and it's still a potential stress on your kidneys. If you do decide to take one pill, make sure to monitor your kidney function closely after taking it and report any changes or symptoms to your doctor. This is just a precaution, but it's always better to be safe than sorry.",
